HEADWORD: Nematogene
<hw>Nem"a*to*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Nemato-</ets> + root of Gr. <?/ to be born.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the dimorphic forms of the species of
Dicyemata, which produced vermiform embryos; -- opposed to
<ant>rhombogene</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

